# POLIS — Project Overview

POLIS is an isometric **city-builder game** whose game lives entirely in a
single self-contained file: `index.html` (~12950 lines). No build step, no
dependencies, no framework — vanilla JS + Canvas 2D. The only external
resources are Google Fonts (loaded via CDN `<link>`). The repo also carries a
headless test suite (`tests/`) and CI, but the game itself ships as that one
file.

## File layout (all in `index.html`)

| Lines | Section |
|-------|---------|
| `1`–`480` | `<head>` + all CSS (custom-property design tokens at `:root`) |
| `480`–`899` | `<body>` — the DOM: canvas `#c`, HUD, panels, modals |
| `899`–`12948` | `<script>` — the entire game engine |

Because everything is global and in one file, **use line ranges and symbol
names to navigate** rather than expecting modules. Line numbers drift as the
file grows, so treat them as approximate and confirm by symbol name. Key entry
points: `loop()` (~11294, the rAF frame loop), `simTick()` (~2542, one game
day), `render()` (~8147, draws a frame).

## Run locally

Just open `index.html` in a browser, or:

```bash
python3 -m http.server 8000   # then visit http://localhost:8000
```

There is nothing to compile or install. Changes are live on reload.

## Deploy

Hosted on **GitHub Pages** at **polis-game.com** (repo `papagel/polis-game`,
branch `main`, served from root). The `CNAME` file pins the custom domain.
Deployment = `git commit` + `git push`; the live site updates within ~1 minute.
Do not rename `index.html` (it is the Pages document root) or delete `CNAME`.

## Working style for this project

- This is a polished, hand-tuned game. Prefer **surgical edits**; preserve the
  terse existing style and the extensive balance-tuning comments.
- A headless Playwright suite lives in `tests/` and runs in CI on every push/PR
  (`.github/workflows/test.yml`). It loads the real `index.html` and asserts
  sim **invariants**, not golden numbers — see `polis-conventions` (Testing).
- See `polis-simulation` for the gameplay/economy model and `polis-conventions`
  for editing rules (save format, redraw flags, balance tables).
